Docker Plugin Installed
jenkins Job Configuration Steps:
Create a New Jenkins Job:

Open Jenkins and click on "New Item" to create a new job.
Enter a name for your job (e.g., "BuildDockerImage") and select "Freestyle project."
Configure Source Code Management:

In the "Source Code Management" section, select your version control system (e.g., Git).
Enter the repository URL and configure authentication if needed.
Configure Build Triggers:

In the "Build Triggers" section, select the trigger that suits your workflow (e.g., "Poll SCM" to poll for changes).
Set the schedule for polling if you selected "Poll SCM."
Configure Build Steps
Configure Post-Build Actions
Save the Jenkins Job Configuration
Run the Jenkins Job Manually